A simple Linux C++ mini project that shows how to:

    Create a static library (libmaths.a)
    Create a dynamic/shared library (liblogger.so)
    Link both in a main project using CMake


Project Structure:

    MiniLibProject/
    ├── CMakeLists.txt
    ├── main.cpp
    ├── maths/
    │   ├── CMakeLists.txt
    │   ├── maths.cpp
    │   └── maths.h
    └── logger/
        ├── CMakeLists.txt
        ├── logger.cpp
        └── logger.h

